e changes don't care about the public school system! They just talk the talk.  They send their children to upper echelon schools that teach to the wealthy and privileged.  There they are taught to become leaders, CEO's, presidents, etc... They need the public schools to teach the masses of workers that follow without questioning. That will do the work to make the rich richer... Call me a cynic but that is how I look at it after all 19 years of teaching! "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="765" language="en" documentId="3312" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="madmm150" date="Aug 29, 2013 7:25PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="4" thumbsDown="0" origId="3312" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="765"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>